text_Original:
I haven't finished the episode yet, so forgive me if these are addressed and I just haven't gotten there yet, but:

- I understand that Meta may want to keep the scanning technology proprietary, but do you think they would be willing to make the product of the scan exportable for use in other platforms?

- Similarly, when he mentioned the file transfer requirements being small, it made me wonder if they have a custom scripting language controlling the avatar's animations, and if that could also be made open source (for use in other platforms)?

Walled gardens deliver the most curated experiences, but they rarely engender broad adoption‚Äîespecially across the business world and in developing nations. If this is, in fact, the future of telepresence, would it not make sense to have both the avatar source (glb, material atlas, shaders, etc.) and the animation scripting language available for any developer to integrate into their immersive meeting application (regardless of inside-out tracked HMD brand)?
text_Display:
I haven't finished the episode yet, so forgive me if these are addressed and I just haven't gotten there yet, but:

- I understand that Meta may want to keep the scanning technology proprietary, but do you think they would be willing to make the product of the scan exportable for use in other platforms?

- Similarly, when he mentioned the file transfer requirements being small, it made me wonder if they have a custom scripting language controlling the avatar's animations, and if that could also be made open source (for use in other platforms)?

Walled gardens deliver the most curated experiences, but they rarely engender broad adoption‚Äîespecially across the business world and in developing nations. If this is, in fact, the future of telepresence, would it not make sense to have both the avatar source (glb, material atlas, shaders, etc.) and the animation scripting language available for any developer to integrate into their immersive meeting application (regardless of inside-out tracked HMD brand)?
